Major News Items in Leading S. African Newspapers
JOHANNESBURG , February 27 ( Xinhua ) -- The following are major news items in leading South African newspapers Friday :
The Citizen
-- There was optimism among South Africa 's government , labor and employer representatives at the gold summit in Johannesburg Thursday afternoon that broad agreements on retrenchments in the gold industry would be reached by Friday .
The Star
-- Most South Africans view crime as a grave threat to the country 's well-being and almost half the population fear for their personal safety , according to the findings of the 1998 Crime Index released by the Institute for Security Studies Thursday .
Business Day
-- Continuing merger speculation and growing confidence about an imminent rates cut catapulted financial stocks on the Johannesburg Stock Exchange Thursday to their 18th record of the year .
